<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="13.[685,1173,460,1543]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[709,824,619,640]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species name is based on the biotic region of the 
<typeStatus box="[880,921,646,667]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">type</typeStatus>
locality, 
<collectingRegion box="[1012,1098,646,667]" country="New Zealand" name="Taranaki" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Taranaki</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="13.[685,1173,460,1543]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[709,814,672,693]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species can be distinguished from the other species of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Broun, 1893 b:" authorityYear="1050" box="[1009,1081,699,720]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Sagola" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirtalis">
<emphasis box="[1009,1081,699,720]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">hirtalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
speciesgroup by the following combination of characters: antennomere 1 elongate, approximately 2.5 times longer than wide; antennomere 4 elongate; posterior frontal fovea elongate; eye small, one-third length of temple; hind wings well-developed; shape of genitalia unique to species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="13.[685,1173,460,1543]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[709,920,885,906]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Description of Male.</emphasis>
Length 
<quantity box="[1017,1103,885,906]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.8" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" unit="mm" value="2.8">2.8 mm</quantity>
. Body yellowish brown, elytra, legs, and maxillary palpi paler (
<figureCitation box="[752,822,938,959]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[197,229,1638,1657]" captionTargetBox="[190,1185,642,1617]" captionTargetId="figure-178@8.[173,1193,624,1622]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 3. Habitus of Sagola species in the hirtalis species-group, dorsal views. a) Sagola hirtalis, b) S. terricola, c) S. convexa, d) S. coromandelensis, e) S. northlandensis, f) S. taranakiensis, g) S. kuscheli, h) S. newtoni, i) S. thorpei, j) S. dugdalei, k) S. thayerae, l) S. hunuaensis, m) S. waikatoensis, n) S. gisbornensis, o) S. weiri, p) S. brookesi. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4907747" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4907747/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 3f</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[849,914,938,959]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Head:</emphasis>
As long as wide, widest across eyes (
<figureCitation box="[820,891,964,985]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[197,229,1638,1657]" captionTargetBox="[190,1185,642,1617]" captionTargetId="figure-178@8.[173,1193,624,1622]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 3. Habitus of Sagola species in the hirtalis species-group, dorsal views. a) Sagola hirtalis, b) S. terricola, c) S. convexa, d) S. coromandelensis, e) S. northlandensis, f) S. taranakiensis, g) S. kuscheli, h) S. newtoni, i) S. thorpei, j) S. dugdalei, k) S. thayerae, l) S. hunuaensis, m) S. waikatoensis, n) S. gisbornensis, o) S. weiri, p) S. brookesi. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4907747" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4907747/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 3f</figureCitation>
). Antennomere 1 approximately 2.5 times longer than wide, 2–3 subquadrate, 4 elongate, approximately 1.5 times longer than wide, 5–6 longer than wide, 7–10 subquadrate. Frontal sulcus deep and reaching hind point of eye from end of frontal rostral lobes. Anterior frontal fovea round, posterior frontal fovea elongate. Eye small and prominent, onethird length of temple. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[931,1016,1177,1198]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Thorax:</emphasis>
Prosternum as long as wide, widest at one-third length. Elytra rectangular (
<figureCitation box="[807,873,1230,1251]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[197,229,1638,1657]" captionTargetBox="[190,1185,642,1617]" captionTargetId="figure-178@8.[173,1193,624,1622]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 3. Habitus of Sagola species in the hirtalis species-group, dorsal views. a) Sagola hirtalis, b) S. terricola, c) S. convexa, d) S. coromandelensis, e) S. northlandensis, f) S. taranakiensis, g) S. kuscheli, h) S. newtoni, i) S. thorpei, j) S. dugdalei, k) S. thayerae, l) S. hunuaensis, m) S. waikatoensis, n) S. gisbornensis, o) S. weiri, p) S. brookesi. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4907747" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4907747/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 3f</figureCitation>
). Hind wings well-developed. Meso- and metathorax trapezoidal, longer than wide. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[749,857,1283,1304]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Abdomen:</emphasis>
Tergite IV with pair of transverse patches of microtrichia reaching middle. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[685,793,1336,1357]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Aedeagus:</emphasis>
Median lobe longer than parameres, with faucet-shaped apical lobe (
<figureCitation box="[984,1047,1363,1384]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[175,207,1144,1163]" captionTargetBox="[166,1166,194,1123]" captionTargetId="figure-247@9.[151,1171,183,1135]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 4. Sagola species in the hirtalis species-group. Aedeagi, dorsal view: a) S. hirtalis, b) S. terricola, c) S. convexa, d) S. coromandelensis, e) S. northlandensis, f) S. taranakiensis, g) S. kuscheli, h) S. newtoni, i) S. thorpei, j) S. dugdalei, k) S. thayerae, l) S. hunuaensis, m) S. waikatoensis, n) S. gisbornensis, o) S. weiri, p) S. brookesi. S. hirtalis: q) Antenna, r) Head, dorsal view, s) Head, ventral view (arrow indicates transverse depression). S. terricola: t) Meso- and metaventrite, u) Male fore femur (arrow indicates semicircular depression). Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4907749" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4907749/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 4f</figureCitation>
). Phallobase of median lobe asymmetrical and triangular (
<figureCitation box="[692,758,1416,1437]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[175,207,1144,1163]" captionTargetBox="[166,1166,194,1123]" captionTargetId="figure-247@9.[151,1171,183,1135]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 4. Sagola species in the hirtalis species-group. Aedeagi, dorsal view: a) S. hirtalis, b) S. terricola, c) S. convexa, d) S. coromandelensis, e) S. northlandensis, f) S. taranakiensis, g) S. kuscheli, h) S. newtoni, i) S. thorpei, j) S. dugdalei, k) S. thayerae, l) S. hunuaensis, m) S. waikatoensis, n) S. gisbornensis, o) S. weiri, p) S. brookesi. S. hirtalis: q) Antenna, r) Head, dorsal view, s) Head, ventral view (arrow indicates transverse depression). S. terricola: t) Meso- and metaventrite, u) Male fore femur (arrow indicates semicircular depression). Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4907749" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4907749/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 4f</figureCitation>
). Right paramere divided into 2 branches, with minor branch crescent-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[1035,1101,1443,1464]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[175,207,1144,1163]" captionTargetBox="[166,1166,194,1123]" captionTargetId="figure-247@9.[151,1171,183,1135]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 4. Sagola species in the hirtalis species-group. Aedeagi, dorsal view: a) S. hirtalis, b) S. terricola, c) S. convexa, d) S. coromandelensis, e) S. northlandensis, f) S. taranakiensis, g) S. kuscheli, h) S. newtoni, i) S. thorpei, j) S. dugdalei, k) S. thayerae, l) S. hunuaensis, m) S. waikatoensis, n) S. gisbornensis, o) S. weiri, p) S. brookesi. S. hirtalis: q) Antenna, r) Head, dorsal view, s) Head, ventral view (arrow indicates transverse depression). S. terricola: t) Meso- and metaventrite, u) Male fore femur (arrow indicates semicircular depression). Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4907749" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4907749/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 4f</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="13.[685,1173,460,1543]" box="[709,1160,1469,1490]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[709,840,1469,1490]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingRegion box="[853,935,1469,1490]" country="New Zealand" name="Taranaki" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Taranaki</collectingRegion>
(
<figureCitation box="[951,1011,1469,1490]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="10.[731,763,905,924]" captionTargetBox="[710,1193,188,881]" captionTargetId="figure-608@10.[707,1194,183,884]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Fig. 5. Known collection localities of New Zealand Sagola species. S. hirtalis: black circles; S. terricola: triangles; S. convexa: black squares; S. coromandelensis: star; S. northlandensis: white circle; S. taranakiensis: white square." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4907753" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4907753/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
: white square).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[685,1173,460,1543]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[709,794,1496,1517]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Habitat.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus box="[853,936,1496,1517]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">holotype</typeStatus>
and only known specimen of this species was collected by sifting litter.
</paragraph>
